         <component>
            <section ID="L0e182ca8-165d-4f1d-80cc-b8ab6b10b674">
               <id root="08ea090f-8e0d-4c1d-976c-d78dcf5d0092"/>
               <code code="34067-9" codeSystem="2.16.840.1.113883.6.1" displayName="INDICATIONS &amp; USAGE SECTION"/>
               <title>
                  <content>
                     <content styleCode="bold">﻿Uses</content>
                  </content>
               </title>
               <text>
                  <paragraph>Temporarily relieves pain from tattoo procedures.</paragraph>
               </text>
               <effectiveTime value="20121003"/>
            </section>
         </component>
         <component>
            <section ID="Lf2adf3ed-f201-424a-bb6f-b8285d61ce65">
               <id root="ad5c4d50-a116-4e43-be03-468144902bcc"/>
               <code code="34068-7" codeSystem="2.16.840.1.113883.6.1" displayName="DOSAGE &amp; ADMINISTRATION SECTION"/>
               <title>
                  <content>
                     <content styleCode="bold">﻿Directions</content>
                  </content>
               </title>
               <text>
                  <paragraph>First test product to sensitivity to skin. </paragraph>
                  <paragraph>Once skin is broken or outline is done, apply derma numb generously to tattooed area.</paragraph>
                  <paragraph>Wait two minutes for anesthetic to take affect, re-apply derma numb to tattoo area as needed through out the tattoo process for comfort. Discontinue use if sensitivity occurs. Do not use on face.</paragraph>
               </text>
               <effectiveTime value="20121003"/>
            </section>
         </component>
         <component>
            <section ID="Ld4e24e68-edaa-40c4-80c9-c04eb869c0d6">
